# Testing and Debugging

## Test Environment

All tests use temporary directories for isolation. `KnowledgeGraph::new` takes a
single path argument — no embedding cache dir, no server required.

```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;
    use tempfile::TempDir;

    fn create_test_graph() -> (KnowledgeGraph, TempDir) {
        let temp_dir = TempDir::new().unwrap();
        let graph = KnowledgeGraph::new(temp_dir.path()).unwrap();
        (graph, temp_dir)
    }
}
```

The SQLite database is created at `<temp_dir>/knowledge.db` automatically.
No `source env.sh`, no model downloads, no running server needed.

