## Storage Tests

`KnowledgeGraphStorage` (SQLite) is tested directly in `src/storage.rs`:

```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;
    use tempfile::TempDir;

    fn create_test_storage() -> (KnowledgeGraphStorage, TempDir) {
        let tmp = TempDir::new().unwrap();
        let storage = KnowledgeGraphStorage::new(tmp.path()).unwrap();
        (storage, tmp)
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_upsert_get_node() {
        let (storage, _tmp) = create_test_storage();
        let meta = ObjectMetadata::new("character".to_string(), "Gandalf".to_string());
        let id = meta.id;
        storage.upsert_node(meta).unwrap();
        let found = storage.get_node(id).unwrap().unwrap();
        assert_eq!(found.name, "Gandalf");
    }
}
```

Key behaviours to test:
- `upsert_node` with `INSERT OR REPLACE` — updating a node must **not** wipe its edges/chunks (the implementation uses `ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE` for this reason)
- `delete_node` — verify `ON DELETE CASCADE` removes edges and chunks
- `search_chunks_fts` — insert a chunk, then query by keyword
- `query_subgraph` — verify BFS hop depth and edge deduplication

