## Debugging

### Log levels
```bash
RUST_LOG=trace                               # Everything
RUST_LOG=debug                               # Development detail
RUST_LOG=info                                # Normal operation (default in demo)
RUST_LOG=u_forge_ai::storage=debug           # Single module
RUST_LOG=u_forge_ai::data_ingestion=warn     # Suppress noisy modules
```

### Structured logging in code
```rust
tracing::info!(
    operation = "upsert_node",
    object_type = %obj.object_type,
    name = %obj.name,
    "Node persisted"
);

tracing::warn!(
    name = %name,
    "Skipping duplicate object during import"
);
```

### Common issues

| Symptom | Likely cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `openssl-sys` compile error | Missing system OpenSSL headers | `apt install pkg-config libssl-dev` (Ubuntu) |
| `Lemonade Server not available` | Server not running or `LEMONADE_URL` not set | `lemonade-server serve` + `export LEMONADE_URL=http://localhost:8000/api/v1` |
| FTS5 search returns nothing | Chunk not yet added for the object | Call `add_text_chunk` before `search_chunks_fts` |
| `database is locked` | Two processes sharing the same `knowledge.db` | Ensure only one writer at a time |
| Import creates 0 edges | Node names in edges don't match node names exactly | Check spelling; `resolve_node_id` does exact-match lookup |
| Schema validation fails on known type | Schema not loaded before validation | Call `SchemaIngestion::load_schemas_from_directory` and `save_schema` first |
| `cannot borrow … as mutable` in test | `TempDir` dropped too early | Bind `_tmp` to a named variable, not `_` |

